		<p>[...] This object cache supposedly caches database queries to disk to reduce CPU and database overhead. This should increase performance in most cases unless your disk I/O performance is very poor, like Dreamhost&#8217;s NFS storage system. This feature seems to be undocumented and had security issues in the past, but is commonly recommended as a safe way of increasing performance. I have heard that the object cache hardly improves performance, but I&#8217;d never imagined that it would slow my site down by 10x or more. [...]</p>

